%N A396591 Decimal expansion of the unique real fixed point of f = Sum_{n>=1} 1/((f+n)^2 + (f+1)).
%C A396591 F0 is the unique positive real solution of the fixed-point equation f = Sum_{n>=1} 1/((f+n)^2 + (f+1)).
%C A396591 Existence and uniqueness follow from the Banach Fixed-Point Theorem: F maps (0,2) into itself and is a contraction.
%C A396591 This constant arises naturally in the study of the nontrivial zeros of the Riemann zeta function, as the finite-scale constant (at gamma=1) of the family phi*(gamma).
%C A396591 No closed-form expression for F0 in terms of classical constants (Pi, e, Euler-Mascheroni gamma, zeta(s)) has been found.
%H A396591 Chaouchi Hamid, <a href="/A396591/a396591.pdf">The Quadratic Bridge: Triangular Numbers, Prime Quadratics, and a Fixed-Point Law for Riemann Zeros</a>, 2026.
%F A396591 Equals lim_{k->oo} f^k(x) for any x in (0,2).
%e A396591 0.6453855490918691350399079767839992299643313449909259...
%t A396591 RealDigits[x /. FindRoot[(-PolyGamma[0, 1-Sqrt[-1-x] + x] + PolyGamma[0, 1+Sqrt[-1-x] + x])/(2*Sqrt[-1-x]) == x, {x, 1}, WorkingPrecision -> 120]][[1]] (* _Amiram Eldar_, May 30 2026 *)
%o A396591 (Python)
%o A396591 from mpmath import mp, findroot, mpf, im, digamma, sqrt, mpc
%o A396591 mp.dps = 60
%o A396591 def F(phi):
%o A396591     c = phi + 1
%o A396591     return im(digamma(mpc(phi+1, sqrt(c)))) / sqrt(c)
%o A396591 print(findroot(lambda p: F(p)-p, mpf('0.645')))
%Y A396591 Cf. A007507, A085846, A030178.
%K A396591 nonn,cons,new
%O A396591 0,1
%A A396591 _Chaouchi Hamid_, May 29 2026
